es within the environmental\ncontext (components 1-2) and any corroborating evidence. 4) Exclusion of false\npositives. The resulting posterior Bayesian probabilities of life's existence\nmap to five confidence levels, ranging from \"very likely\" (90-100%) to \"very\nunlikely\" ($\\le$10%) inhabited.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 18 May 2017 01:04:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 8 Aug 2017 00:52:12 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 3 May 2018 22:29:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-07"}
